result.execSummary:
The defendant Isaiah R Kumbera was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Computer Message-Threaten/Injury or Harm, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.0125(2)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

09:38 AM; Case called for Bail/bond hearing.  Defendant Isaiah R Kumbera in court, in custody at WCJ, with attorney Eryn M Menden.   Lindsey Hirt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court notes the bail motion was set over to today to allow for victim notification rights.  Court confirms with the State victim rights have been complied with.  Atty. Menden presents arguments; she is asking court to lower the cash bail to $1,000.00.  State objects and presents arguments.  Atty. Menden presents additional statements.  Court places its findings on the record.  For reasons placed on the record the court denies the motion to modify bail; bail to remain as previously set.  Atty. Menden requests the court allow for Huber release.  Court denies that request.  Court inquires how the matter is proceeding.  Atty. Menden presents statements, she believes all matters are set to resolve and requests a plea and sentencing date in a couple of weeks.  Court adjourns for plea and sentencing.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for May 5, 2022 at 10:30 am.
Bail/bond hearing on April 14, 2022 at 09:30 am.
